<subSubSection id="1FE5655FFFE1416CCA81EA72FB252450" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE1416CCA81EA72FE6F235C" blockId="23.[151,1437,690,1077]" box="[199,477,798,825]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE1416CCA81EA72FEE1235D" bold="true" box="[199,339,798,824]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">References:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE1416CCB1CEA73FE6F235C" author="Hemp, C." box="[346,477,799,825]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" refId="ref16956" refString="Hemp, C. (2021) A Field Guide to the Bushcrickets, Wetas and Raspy Crickets of Tanzania and Kenya. Senckenberg Gesellschaft fur Naturforschung, Frankfurt, 451 pp." type="book" year="2021">Hemp 2021</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE1416CCA81EA2EFF6D23AC" blockId="23.[151,1437,690,1077]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE1416CCA81EA2EFED02339" bold="true" box="[199,354,834,860]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Bioacoustics.</emphasis>
Tegmina (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE1416CCB9CEA2FFDAF2338" box="[474,541,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[161,1415,290,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-72@5.[151,1436,273,1718]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left male tegmina of Acanthoplus discoidalis (CH8946), Acanthoproctus cervinus (CH8947), Hetrodes pupus (CHelb8948), Enyaliopsis bloyeti (CH8853), E. carolinus (CH8625), E. ephippiatus (CH7737), E. jennae (damaged; CH8267), Gymnoproctus rammei (CH8763), Eugasteroides loricatus (CH7352), Spalacomimus stettinenesis, S. talpa (CH7354), S. verruciferus (CH7188). Scale 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392715/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), stridulatory file (
<tableCitation id="1A7D036FFFE1416CC8A9EA2FFCF02338" box="[751,834,835,861]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,239,332,356]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. Body dimensions and characteristics of stridulatory files in Hetrodini" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0380665CFFF54178CAD1E820FC402101" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" tableUuid="0380665CFFF54178CAD1E820FC402101">Table 1</tableCitation>
), and spectrum of the song (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE1416CCEC5EA2FFB74233B" box="[1155,1222,835,862]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[171,1410,201,1247]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[151,1436,181,1263]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Power spectra of male calling songs in Hetrodini species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392725/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) do not show large differences to the typical 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE1416CCBFCEA0BFD9723E4" authorityName=", Kowalski &amp; Lakes-Harlan" authorityYear="2010" box="[442,549,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Hetrodini">Hetrodini</taxonomicName>
pattern. The calling song (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE1416CC91DEA0BFC0C23E4" box="[859,958,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1322,1346]" captionTargetBox="[156,1433,260,1291]" captionTargetId="figure-48@14.[151,1436,237,1299]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Oscillograms of the calling songs in the genera Eugaster, Eugasteroides and Spalacomimus (figures of S. liberianus based on figures and data from literature; see text). A Eugaster guyoni, B Eugaster spinulosa, C Eugasteroides loricatus, D Spalacomimus liberianus, E Spalacomimus magnus, F Spalacomimus stettinensis, G Spalacomimus talpa, H Spalacomimus verruciferus, I Spalacomimus spec. near verruciferus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392739/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
) consists of long series of echemes (ERR 0.3 Hz; as song 
<typeStatus id="88448876FFE1416CCB09EAE7FECD23C0" box="[335,383,907,933]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">type</typeStatus>
C 
<quantity id="90079B31FFE1416CCBD8EAE7FE7423C0" box="[414,454,907,933]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="23" pageNumber="474" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE1416CCB88EAE7FDA023C0" box="[462,530,906,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1254,1278]" captionTargetBox="[158,1423,198,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[151,1436,181,1231]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Oscillograms of song types in Hetrodini. Song consisting A of long trills (Cosmoderus femoralis CH8627), B of broken trills (including transitions to long echemes; B1 Spalacomimus talpa, B2 Enyaliopsis jennae, B3 Enyaliopsis ephippiatus) or C of regularly repeated echemes (C1 Spalacomimus spec. near verruciferus, C2 Eugaster guyoni). 1-min-sections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392721/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). An echeme has 48 syllables which are repeated at a rate of 26 Hz (all data for 21ºC).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE1416CCA81EABEFB252450" blockId="23.[151,1437,690,1077]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE1416CCA81EABEFE8F2389" bold="true" box="[199,317,978,1004]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Genitalia.</emphasis>
The titillator is very massive with long basal parts (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE1416CC93AEABFFC532388" box="[892,993,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1046,1070]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,272,1023]" captionTargetId="figure-69@15.[151,1436,272,1023]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 11. Titillators in the genus Spalacomimus. A S. magnus (Gulwe), B S. stettinensis (Lambo Estate), C S. stettinensis (neotype), D S. talpa (Lembeni), E S. verruciferus (Lake Chala), F S. spec. near verruciferus (Lossogonoi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392741/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
). Its main part is nearly as wide as long, a little narrowed at base and showing a broad and flat or broadly rounded tip. Also the lateral sclerites are well-developed. The titillator of our specimen agrees very well with that of the 
<typeStatus id="88448876FFE1416CC9FAED77FBA72450" box="[956,1045,1051,1077]" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">neotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE1416CCE62ED77FB3B2450" box="[1060,1161,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1046,1070]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,272,1023]" captionTargetId="figure-69@15.[151,1436,272,1023]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 11. Titillators in the genus Spalacomimus. A S. magnus (Gulwe), B S. stettinensis (Lambo Estate), C S. stettinensis (neotype), D S. talpa (Lembeni), E S. verruciferus (Lake Chala), F S. spec. near verruciferus (Lossogonoi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392741/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="474">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
